# Project Context

This file provides persistent instructions to Radium agents. Customize it with your project's guidelines, standards, and practices.

## Project Overview

Describe your project's purpose, goals, and key characteristics here.

## Coding Standards

Define your project's coding standards:

- Language-specific conventions
- Code formatting rules
- Naming conventions
- Comment and documentation standards

## Testing Requirements

Specify testing expectations:

- Test coverage goals
- Testing frameworks and tools
- Test organization and naming
- Integration vs unit testing strategy

## Architecture Guidelines

Document architectural principles:

- Design patterns to follow or avoid
- Module organization
- Dependency management
- Performance considerations

## Development Workflow

Outline your development process:

- Branch naming conventions
- Commit message format
- Code review process
- Release procedures

## Additional Context

Add any other information that agents should know:

- Common patterns and practices
- Known pitfalls to avoid
- Project-specific tools or utilities
- Team conventions

## Importing Other Files

You can organize context across multiple files using imports:

```markdown
@docs/coding-standards.md
@docs/architecture.md
```

This allows you to:
- Keep the main context file focused
- Share context files across projects
- Organize complex guidelines into logical sections

## Tips

- Keep instructions clear and actionable
- Update this file as your project evolves
- Use markdown structure for readability
- Reference external documentation when appropriate

